ğŸ§ª 3. Useful String Methods
Method	Description	Example
.upper() |	Converts to uppercase	'abc'.upper() â†’ 'ABC'
.lower() |	Converts to lowercase	'ABC'.lower() â†’ 'abc'
.strip() |	Removes whitespace from edges	' hello '.strip() â†’ 'hello'
.replace() |	Replaces substring	'abc'.replace('a','A') â†’ 'Abc'
.split() | Splits by a delimiter into a list	'a,b,c'.split(',') â†’ ['a','b','c']
.find()	| Finds first index of substring	'hello'.find('l') â†’ 2
.startswith() |	Checks if string starts with prefix	'python'.startswith('py') â†’ True
.endswith() |	Checks if string ends with suffix	'python'.endswith('on') â†’ True

